article.headline: Marist 79, Wright St. 64
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y., (AP) -- Senior guard Louie McCroskey scored 24 points to lead Marist to a 79-64 win over Wright State Saturday. McCroskey shot 10-for-19 from the field, 3-for-8 from three-point range and 1-for-1 from the free-throw line. He also collected eight rebounds and had three assists, a blocked shot and a steal. Freshman guard Jay Gavin added 10 points in 16 minutes off the bench for Marist (5-3). Senior center Spongy Benjamin had seven points and a game-high nine rebounds. Todd Brown paced Wright State (1-2) with 12 points.
